{
  "texts": [
    "We also do not limit our search to computer science works only, as recent LLMs have been investigated by researchers from many other domains, e.g.",
    "healthcare (Kung et al., 2023), psychology (Cai et al., 2023) and education (Szefer and Deshpande, 2023).",
    "Since the ChatGPT models are our primary focus, we limit our search to works between late November 2022 (when the first model was publicly released) and early October 2023.",
    "Among all the papers, we first do a preliminary screening, assessing if they effectively run GPT-3.5 or GPT-4 in any form. foot_6",
    "To assess which work effectively leaked data to ChatGPT, we refer to OpenAI's data usage policy, foot_7, which explicitly mentions the use of users' data for model training: Therefore, only the work interacting with the models through the web interface foot_8 is considered to leak data."
  ]
}